      "name": "backend/services/anonymization_service.py",
      "entityType": "Service",
      "observations": [
        "S3-001: Anonymization Service for document anonymization integration",
        "Defines AnonymizationService class with singleton pattern",
        "Defines AnonymizationResult dataclass for anonymization results",
        "Provides anonymize_image(base64_image: str) async method for image anonymization",
        "Provides check_service_health() async method for service health monitoring",
        "Integrates with external anonymization service at localhost:5000/ai-analysis",
        "Defines ANONYMIZATION_SERVICE_URL constant (API_URL = http://localhost:5000/ai-analysis)",
        "Defines SECRET_KEY constant for API authentication",
        "Defines TIMEOUT_SECONDS constant (30 seconds)",
        "Uses aiohttp for async HTTP requests to external service",
        "Handles PII detection and black box masking for identity documents"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "backend/services/anonymization_service.py::AnonymizationService",
      "entityType": "Class",
      "observations": [
        "S3-001: Singleton service class for document anonymization",
        "Implements singleton pattern via __new__ method with _instance class variable",
        "Class variables: _instance, API_URL, SECRET_KEY, TIMEOUT_SECONDS",
        "Methods: anonymize_image(base64_image: str) -> AnonymizationResult, check_service_health() -> bool",
        "anonymize_image() validates input format and adds data URI prefix if missing",
        "anonymize_image() sends POST request with image and mode:default payload",
        "anonymize_image() handles 200, 401, 400, and other status codes with appropriate error messages",
        "check_service_health() pings service root endpoint with 5s timeout",
        "Uses aiohttp.ClientSession for async HTTP communication",
        "_extract_base64_data() method extracts raw base64 data and mime type from data URI",
        "_apply_black_boxes() method draws black rectangles over detected PII areas using PIL",
        "Uses PIL (Pillow) Image and ImageDraw for local image manipulation",
        "Converts images to RGB mode for drawing if necessary (RGBA, LA, P modes)",
        "Detection response format: {\"data\": {\"field_name\": [{\"confidence\": X, \"coordinate\": [x, y, w, h]}]}}",
        "Timeout increased to TIMEOUT_SECONDS = 60 for large images",
        "Returns original image if no detections found (detections_count = 0)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "backend/services/anonymization_service.py::AnonymizationResult",
      "entityType": "Dataclass",
      "observations": [
        "S3-001: Dataclass for anonymization operation results",
        "Attributes: success (bool), anonymized_image (Optional[str]), detections_count (int), error (Optional[str])",
        "anonymized_image contains base64-encoded image with data URI prefix",
        "detections_count indicates number of PII fields detected and masked",
        "Used as return type for AnonymizationService.anonymize_image() method"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "backend/tools/anonymization_tool.py",
      "entityType": "Tool",
      "observations": [
        "S3-001: Anonymization Tool for document anonymization operations",
        "Exports anonymize_document(file_path: str) -> AnonymizationToolResult async function",
        "Exports is_supported_format(file_path: str) -> bool function for format validation",
        "Exports get_supported_formats() -> list[str] function to list supported formats",
        "Defines AnonymizationToolResult dataclass for operation results",
        "Defines SUPPORTED_EXTENSIONS constant: {'.png', '.jpg', '.jpeg', '.gif', '.bmp', '.webp'}",
        "Defines MIME_TYPES constant mapping extensions to MIME types",
        "Helper functions: _get_anonymized_filename(), _image_to_base64(), _base64_to_image()",
        "Integrates with AnonymizationService for actual anonymization",
        "Imports AnonymizationService and AnonymizationResult from backend.services.anonymization_service",
        "S5-006: Added render_metadata field to AnonymizationToolResult",
        "anonymize_document() now accepts document_id and register_render parameters",
        "When register_render=True, registers anonymized file as render via file_service",
        "Supports optional render registration for document manifest integration"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "backend/tools/anonymization_tool.py::anonymize_document",
      "entityType": "Function",
      "observations": [
        "S3-001: Main async function for document anonymization",
        "Signature: async anonymize_document(file_path: str) -> AnonymizationToolResult",
        "Step 1: Validates and converts image to base64 using _image_to_base64()",
        "Step 2: Calls AnonymizationService().anonymize_image(base64_image)",
        "Step 3: Generates output path using _get_anonymized_filename()",
        "Step 4: Saves anonymized image using _base64_to_image()",
        "Returns AnonymizationToolResult with original_path, anonymized_path, detections_count",
        "Original file remains unchanged"
      ]
    },
